description:
## Severity
Major
## Dimension
concurrency
## Location
src/subagent.rs:1407-1414 (execute_agent_output_tool block path)
## Violation
The blocking `agent_output` poll loop is:

```rust
if block && !agent.finished.load(Ordering::SeqCst) {
    let start = std::time::Instant::now();
    let timeout = std::time::Duration::from_mins(5);
    while !agent.finished.load(Ordering::SeqCst) && start.elapsed() < timeout {
        std::thread::sleep(std::time::Duration::from_millis(500));
    }
}
```

`execute_agent_output_tool` is invoked from `execute_tool_with_memory` which is called from inside `run_subagent`'s async loop (see src/subagent.rs:936). `std::thread::sleep` parks the entire OS thread — under tokio's multi-thread runtime it blocks one worker for up to 5 minutes; under current_thread it deadlocks the whole runtime, including the background agent we're waiting on (so the loop can never complete).
## Mandated refactor
Convert the blocking wait to an async path: expose `execute_agent_output_tool_async` returning a `Future`, use `tokio::time::sleep`, and have the calling tool dispatcher await it. Until the dispatcher is async, gate the block path with `tokio::task::block_in_place` AND require multi-thread runtime, or reject `block: true` outright.
